         <div xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve" type="translation">
            <p>
               <milestone n="1" unit="line"/> To Gaius Trebius Justus, centurion, <milestone n="3" rend="break" unit="line"/> from Petermouthis son of Heracleus of Euhemeria, a farmer of state land and collector of public dues, 
also a farmer on the estate of Antonia wife of Drusus. <milestone n="8" unit="line"/> On the 2nd of the present month Pachon of the 1st year of Gaius Caesar Imperator, 
as I was talking to Papontos son of Orsenouphis and Apion called Kapareis, <milestone n="15" rend="break" unit="line"/> shepherds, concerning what they owe me as damages for grazing by their flocks, 
they belaboured me with blows, shamelessly refusing to pay, and I lost 40 silver drachmae which I had with me from the sale of opium, and my belt. 
<milestone n="23" rend="break" unit="line"/> Wherefore I pray to obtain succour, in order that no public interest may suffer. Farewell.
            </p>
